name: neynar-free-tier
description: Neynar Farcaster API free tier constraints, workarounds, and patterns. Use when building Farcaster apps/snaps without a paid Neynar plan.
---

## Free Tier Endpoint Availability

**Only `user/bulk` is free.** Everything else requires a paid plan.

| Endpoint | Free? | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `GET /user/bulk?fids=1,2,3` | ✓ | Batch user lookup by FID (up to ~100 per call) |
| `GET /user/trending` | ✗ | PaymentRequired |
| `GET /feed?feed_type=filter&...` | ✗ | PaymentRequired |
| `GET /feed?feed_type=global_trending` | ✗ | PaymentRequired |
| `GET /casts?fid=N` | ✗ | PaymentRequired |
| `GET /following?fid=N` | ✗ | PaymentRequired |
| `GET /followers?fid=N` | ✗ | PaymentRequired |
| `GET /user/search?q=...` | ✗ | PaymentRequired |
| `GET /reactions/cast?...` | ✗ | PaymentRequired |
| `GET /channel?...` | ✗ | PaymentRequired |

## Workaround: Seed Pool Pattern

Since you can't dynamically discover users via trending/feeds, maintain a **seed pool of known FIDs**:

```typescript
const SEED_FIDS: number[] = [
  3, 56, 185, 194, 226, 239, 276, 341, 576, 756,
  // ... expand as needed
];

// Fetch in batches of 20 via user/bulk
async function buildPool(fids: number[]): Promise<User[]> {
  const users: User[] = [];
  for (let i = 0; i < fids.length; i += 20) {
    const batch = fids.slice(i, i + 20);
    const data = await neynarFetch(`/user/bulk?fids=${batch.join(",")}`);
    users.push(...(data?.users ?? []));
  }
  return users;
}
```

**What you CAN do with free tier:**
- Qualify users by: account age, Neynar score, follower/following ratio, follower count
- Enrich profiles with: display name, bio, pfp, verification status, power badge
- You CANNOT: analyze post content, check following graphs, search users, get trending

## Image URL Gotcha

Neynar profile pictures from `imagedelivery.net` don't have file extensions:

```
https://imagedelivery.net/BXluQx4ige9GuW0Ia56BHw/abc123/rectcrop3
```

**Farcaster snap validator REQUIRES URLs ending with `.jpg`, `.jpeg`, `.png`, `.gif`, or `.webp`.**

Fix: append `.jpg` to imagedelivery.net URLs:

```typescript
function safeImageUrl(url: string): string {
  if (!url) return fallbackUrl;
  const exts = [".jpg", ".jpeg", ".png", ".gif", ".webp"];
  const lower = url.toLowerCase().split("?")[0];
  if (exts.some(ext => lower.endsWith(ext))) return url;
  if (url.includes("imagedelivery.net")) return url + ".jpg";
  return fallbackUrl;
}
```

## Qualification Without Casts

Without the casts endpoint, you can't verify post count or original content. Simplify qualification to free-tier data:

```typescript
function qualifyUser(user: NeynarUser) {
  const age = daysSince(user.registered_at);
  const score = user.score ?? 0;
  const ratio = user.following_count > 0
    ? user.follower_count / user.following_count
    : user.follower_count > 0 ? 999 : 0;

  return age >= 180        // 6+ months
    && score >= 0.42        // reasonable Neynar score
    && ratio >= 0.15        // not a follow-back bot
    && user.follower_count >= 10;
}
```

## API Key Handling

When deploying to host.neynar.app, the deploy API returns the API key in JSON. The CLI tool output may truncate long JSON — capture the full response programmatically:

```python
result = subprocess.run(["curl", "-s", "-X", "POST", ...], capture_output=True)
data = json.loads(result.stdout)
full_key = data["apiKey"]  # full UUID format
```

## Auth Header

```bash
-H "api_key: YOUR_KEY"  # NOT "Authorization: Bearer"
```
